msgid ""
"PEP 8011 was rejected `by a core developer vote "
"<https://discuss.python.org/t/python-governance-vote-"
"december-2018-results/546/>`__ described in PEP 8001 on Monday, December "
"17, 2018."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:42
msgid "PEP 8016 and the governance model it describes were chosen instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:45
msgid "Open discussion points"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:47
msgid ""
"Various tweaks to the parameters of this PEP are allowed during the "
"governance discussion process, such as the exact responsibilities of the "
"Trio, term lengths of service, voting procedures, and trio disbandment. "
"These will be codified by the time the PEP is ready to be voted on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:52
msgid ""
"It is allowed, and perhaps even expected, that as experience is gained "
"with this model, these parameters may be tweaked in order to provide for "
"a smoother governing process. The process for tweaking these parameters "
"will generally be the same voting process as described in PEP 8001."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:59
msgid "Roles and responsibilities of the leadership trio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:61
msgid ""
"Be open, considerate, respectful. In other words, adhering to The PSF's "
"code of conduct."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:62
msgid ""
"Pronounce on PEPs, either as a team, or individually if the other trio "
"members agree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:63
msgid ""
"Provide vision and leadership for Python, the programming language and "
"the community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:64
msgid "Understand their own limitation, and seek advice whenever necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:65
msgid "Provide mentorship to the next generation of leaders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:66
msgid "Be a Python core developer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:67
msgid ""
"Be a voting member of The PSF (one of Contributing / Manager / Fellow / "
"Supporter). [2]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:68
msgid ""
"Understand that Python is not just a language but also a community. They "
"need to be aware of issues in Python not just the technical aspects, but "
"also other issues in the community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:71
msgid ""
"Facilitate the formation of specialized working groups within Core "
"Python. See \"formation of specialized working groups\" section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:73
msgid ""
"Set good example of behavior, culture, and tone to Python community. Just"
" as Python looks at and learn from other communities for inspiration, "
"other communities will look at Python and learn from us."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:79
msgid "Authority of the trio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:81
msgid ""
"To be clear, in case any dispute arises: the trio has the final authority"
" to pronounce on PEPs (except for the governance PEP), to decide whether "
"a particular decision requires a PEP, and to resolve technical disputes "
"in general. The trio's authority does not include changing the governance"
" itself, or other non-technical disputes that may arise; these should be "
"handled through the process described in PEP 8001."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:91
msgid "What are NOT considered as the role responsibilities of the trio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:93
msgid ""
"The following are not the expected out of the trio, however they can do "
"these if they wish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:95
msgid ""
"They are not always the ones coming up with all the ideas, vision, "
"problems to solve, and what not. The trio will be open and accepting "
"suggestions from core developers and community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:98
msgid ""
"Day to day bug reports do not require the trio to intervene. Any core "
"devs are able to make decisions, but will defer to the respective focused"
" workgroups, and will eventually defer to the trio when there are major "
"disagreements among core developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:101
msgid "Does not run / decide on Python language summit and its logistics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:102
msgid "Does not run / decide on Python core sprint and its logistics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:103
msgid ""
"Does not handle CoC cases. Those are responsibilities of the PSF CoC "
"workgroup, but will speak out if they witness those cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:105
msgid ""
"Does not make decisions about other Python implementations (Cython, "
"IronPython, etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:106
msgid "Does not run / decide on Python conferences and its logistics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:107
msgid ""
"Not an evangelist of Python. The trio is not expected to preach/advertise"
" for Python. They can if they want to, but not expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:109
msgid ""
"Not an educator of Python. The trio is not expected to be the ones "
"teaching/writing about Python. They can if they want to, but not "
"expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:111
msgid ""
"The trio is not expected to be available 24/7, 365 days a year. They are "
"free to decide for themselves their availability for Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:113
msgid "Not a PEP editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:117
msgid "Guidelines for the formation of the trio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:119
msgid ""
"The success of this governance model relies on the members of the trio, "
"and the ability of the trio members to collaborate and work well "
"together."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:122
msgid ""
"The three people need to have similar vision to Python, and each can have"
" different skills that complement one another."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:125
msgid ""
"With such a team, disagreements and conflict should be rare, but can "
"still happen. We will need to trust the people we select that they are "
"able to resolve this among themselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:129
msgid ""
"When it comes to select the members of the trio, instead of nominating "
"various individuals and choosing the top three, core developers will "
"nominate trios and vote for groups of threes who they believe can form "
"this united trio. There is no restriction that an individual can only be "
"nominated in one slate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:134
msgid "This PEP will not name or nominate anyone into the trio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:136
msgid ""
"Only once this PEP is accepted, any active core developers (who are "
"eligible to vote) can submit nomination of groups of three."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:139
msgid ""
"Once this PEP is accepted and core devs have submitted their nominations,"
" voting can begin, and the voting mechanism described in PEP 8001 will be"
" used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:142
msgid "Qualities desired out of the trio:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:144
msgid "Be a Python core developer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:145
msgid ""
"Be a voting PSF member (one of Contributing / Manager / Fellow / "
"Supporter). [2]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:146
msgid "Be a member of the community with good standing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:147
msgid ""
"Adhere to The PSF's code of conduct (Be open, considerate, and "
"respectful). [1]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:148
msgid "Be willing to accept the said roles and responsibilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:149
msgid "Able to communicate and articulate their thoughts effectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:151
msgid "The following are not requirements when considering someone into the trio:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:153
msgid "\"Experience being a BDFL of something\" is not a requirement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:154
msgid "\"Be a genius\" is not a requirement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:157
msgid "Diversity and inclusivity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:159
msgid ""
"The core Python development team fully supports the Python Software "
"Foundation’s diversity statement, and welcomes participation and "
"contribution from people from diverse backgrounds. When nominating people"
" to be part of the trio, Python core developers will take every effort "
"into including members from underrepresented group into consideration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:165
msgid ""
"Ideally, nomination should include and reflect the diversity of core "
"Python contributors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:169
msgid "Sustainability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:171
msgid ""
"Lack of employer support or lack of luxury of free time should not be a "
"factor when identifying who should be in a trio. If there are individuals"
" who the core devs have identified as having the necessary skills for "
"being a member of the trio, but they are unable to do it because of lack "
"of time, lack of financial support, then we should open discussion with "
"The PSF or other parties into providing the needed support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:180
msgid "Additional guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:182
msgid ""
"When nominating someone other than yourself, please first ask privately "
"if they are ok with being nominated, and if they are ok with nominated in"
" that group of three. This is so people don’t feel pressured to accept "
"nomination just because it happens publicly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:188
msgid "Why not other governance model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:190
msgid ""
"Core Python community are familiar with the singular BDFL model for over "
"two decades, it was a model that has \"worked\" for Python. Shifting to a"
" completely different model all of the sudden, could be disruptive to the"
" stability of the community. However, the community can continue to "
"evolve in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:196
msgid ""
"If this PEP is chosen, it is not meant to be the only governance model "
"for Python going forward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:199
msgid ""
"This PEP proposed a transition into a community led by a group of people "
"(although small), while also introducing the concept of additional "
"specialized workgroups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:204
msgid "Why not more than three"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:206
msgid "*Too many chefs spoil the soup.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:208
msgid ""
"The goal of having a leadership team is for team Python core developers "
"to be able to come to consensus and decisions. The larger the leadership "
"team is, the more difficult it will be in coming up with decision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:212
msgid ""
"This is also for the benefit of the members of the trio. Learning to "
"collaborate with other people in a team is not something that happen "
"organically and takes a lot of effort. It is expected that members of the"
" trio will be part of the team for a long-term period. Having to deal "
"with two other people is probably difficult enough. We want the trio to "
"be able to do their duties and responsibilities as efficient as possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:219
msgid ""
"The more people in the group, the more difficult it is to try to come up "
"with time to meet, discuss, and coming up with decision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:224
msgid "Roles and responsibilities of Python Core Developers to the trio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:226
msgid ""
"Be open, considerate, and respectful. In other words, adhere to The PSF's"
" Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:227
msgid ""
"Decisions and pronouncements made by individual members of the trio are "
"to be seen as authoritative and coming from the trio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:229
msgid ""
"Once the trio has pronounced a decision, core devs will be supportive, "
"even if they were not supportive in the beginning (before the trio made "
"such decision)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:231
msgid ""
"Continue with day-to-day decision making in the bug tracker, and defer to"
" the trio if there is major disagreement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:233
msgid ""
"Python core developers do not handle CoC cases, those are "
"responsibilities of the CoC workgroup, but will speak out if they witness"
" those cases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:235
msgid ""
"Aware that they are part of the larger Python community, not just the "
"technical aspect of it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:237
msgid ""
"Be a voting PSF member (one of Contributing / Manager / Fellow / "
"Supporter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:238
msgid "Set good example of behavior, culture, and tone to Python community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:242
msgid "Term Limit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:244
msgid ""
"The trio is not expected to serve for life, however a longer term is "
"desired. The purpose of longer term service is to avoid unnecessary "
"churns of needing to “elect”, and to provide stability and consistency in"
" the language and the community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:249
msgid ""
"Currently, Python release managers hold their position for 5 years (one "
"release cycle), and that seems to work so far. Therefore, this PEP "
"proposes that the trio hold their position for 5 years."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:255
msgid "Succession planning of the trio (open for discussion)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:257
msgid ""
"The trio should notify core devs of their intention to "
"disband/retire/quit from their roles at least one year in advance, to "
"allow for them to actively mentor and train the next generation of "
"successors, and to avoid power vacuum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:261
msgid ""
"The trio do not necessarily have to be the ones choosing who the next "
"leaders will be."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:264
msgid ""
"This PEP does not enforce that the same governance model be chosen for "
"the next generation. Python as language and community can continue to "
"evolve. By giving one year advance notice to disband, the trio is giving "
"the core Python community an opportunity to reflect on the "
"success/failure of this governance model, and choose a different "
"governance model if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:270
msgid ""
"However, the next governance model and leaders should be chosen/elected "
"within one year after the trio announced their desire to disband."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:273
msgid ""
"If it was decided to continue with this model of governance, the next "
"generation of trio will be nominated and elected similar to how the first"
" trio were nominated/chosen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:277
msgid ""
"The trio should act as advisor/mentor to the next generation chosen "
"leaders for at least X months."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:280
msgid ""
"Since future trio will be chosen out of Python core developers, it will "
"make sense for future Python core developers to possess some but not "
"necessarily all, qualities of the trio as laid out in this PEP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:284
msgid ""
"Therefore, the guidelines for selecting trio members can also be used as "
"guidelines when identifying future Python core developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:288
msgid "Scenario if one member of the trio needs to quit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:290
msgid ""
"Effective governance models provide off-ramps or temporary breaks for "
"leaders who need to step down or pause their leadership service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:293
msgid "What if one member of the chosen trio has to quit, for unforeseen reasons?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:295
msgid "There are several possible options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:297
msgid "The remaining duo can select another member to fill in the role"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:298
msgid "The trio can choose to disband, core developers can nominate other trios"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:299
msgid "Core developers can choose a different governance model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:301
msgid ""
"Since the trio were elected as a slate and so the loss of one breaks that"
" unit that was elected. Therefore, a new election should be held."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:305
msgid ""
"Formation of working groups/area of expertise/ownership (previously BDFL "
"delegate)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:307
msgid "(Open for discussion)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:309
msgid ""
"Certain areas and topic of Core Python and Python community require "
"leaders with specific skills of specialty. It will be recommended that "
"there will be several working groups with more authority in that specific"
" area to assist the trio in making decisions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:314
msgid ""
"The role of these \"specialized work groups/council\" is to be the final "
"decision maker for controversial discussions that arise in their "
"respective areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:317
msgid ""
"These working groups should be small (3-5 people), for similar reasons "
"that the leadership trio is a small group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:320
msgid ""
"These working groups should consist of both Python core developers and "
"external experts. This is to ensure that decision made does not favor "
"only Python core developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:324
msgid ""
"Python Core developers will defer decisions to these working groups on "
"their respective topic. However these groups will answer/defer to the "
"trio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:327
msgid ""
"These working groups can be selected and members voted only after this "
"PEP gets accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:330
msgid ""
"If this PEP is accepted, the working group can be decided within a year "
"or two after the PEP's acceptance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:333
msgid ""
"When selecting members of these special work groups, the trio will take "
"every effort into including members from underrepresented group into "
"consideration. Ideally, the workgroup members should include and reflect "
"the diversity of the wider Python community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:338
msgid ""
"Members of this workgroup do not need to be a Python core developer, but "
"they need to be at least a basic member of the PSF [2]_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:341
msgid "These workgroup are active as long as the trio are active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:343
msgid "Several suggested working groups to start:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:345
msgid "Documentation of CPython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:346
msgid "Security of CPython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:347
msgid "Performance of CPython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:349
msgid ""
"The workgroup can be seen as having similar role as the previously known "
"role of \"BDFL-delegate\" or PEP czars. The difference is, instead of "
"appointing a single person as decision maker, there will be a small team "
"of decision makers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:353
msgid ""
"Another difference with the previous \"BDFL-delegate\" role, the group "
"can be active as long as the trio is active, as opposed to only when "
"there is a PEP that requires their expertise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:357
msgid "When the trio disbands, these workgroups are disbanded too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:361
msgid "Why these workgroups are necessary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:363
msgid ""
"This is an effort to 'refactor the large role' of the previous Python "
"BDFL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:366
msgid "Affirmation as being a member of the PSF"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:368
msgid ""
"This PEP proposes that core developers and the trio members self-certify "
"themselves as being a member of The PSF."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:371
msgid ""
"Being part of the PSF means being part of the Python community, and "
"support The PSF's mission and diversity statement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:374
msgid ""
"By being a member of The PSF, Python core developers declare their "
"support for Python and agree to the community Code of Conduct."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:377
msgid "For more details of The PSF membership, see: PSF Membership FAQ [2]_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:380
msgid "Reasoning for choosing the name trio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:382
msgid "Not to be confused with Python trio (an async library)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pep-8011.rst:384
msgid ""
"The \"trio\" is short and easy to pronounce, unlike other words that are "
"long and can have negative interpretations, like triad, trinity, "
"triumvirate, threesome, etc."
msgstr ""

